content:
Create a remote connection using the Salesforce External connector to sync data from another Salesforce org to CRM Analytics.

Restricted API access isn't supported for Salesforce Output and External connectors. Enable the Use Any API Client permission for the user creating the connector.

Create the Connection
On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector, and click Next.
Enter the connector settings:
Connection Name: Identifies the connections.
Developer Name: API name for the connection.
Description: Description
Username: User name used to connect to external Salesforce org for sync of objects and fields.
API Type: The API to use (SOAP or BULKV2).
Service URL: Login URL for the external org.
Password: Password for the user specified in Username.

Filter Data Synced to CRM Analytics

Exclude unnecessary or sensitive data from syncing to CRM Analytics with data sync filters. Enter a filter using a SOQL WHERE clause expression, such as "(FiscalQuarter = 2 OR FiscalQuarter = 3) AND Amount > 1000 AND Amount <= 20000".

Salesforce External Connector Considerations

* Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
* This connector can sync up to 20 million rows or 10 GB per object, whichever limit it reaches first.
* Use of the API Type BULKV2 is only supported with API version 50.0 and above.

To troubleshoot connectivity issues between Salesforce orgs, review your org IP address restrictions and consider disabling the setting "Lock sessions to the IP address from which they originated" in both orgs.
title: Setting Up Salesforce External Connection
